Very simply, because the leaders of the Arabs in the West Bank and Gaza (as well as Hizballah in Lebanon) have a lot to lose by fomenting violence. That is the key to peace – creating a situation where the downside of attacks is much greater than the upside of what could be accomplished by violence. Choosing violence (on a macro level) Â has nothing to do with “justice” or “rights” or anything like that – it is a simple cost/benefit analysis of what can be gained versus what can be lost.
